Ekitike or if playing the free hit chip is the play?</b></p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Ekitike has the better fixtures but a start isnt guaranteed and 90 minutes is very unlikely I come to you with the age-old question: Mo Salah or Erling Haaland? </b></p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">This one feels impossible to answer at the moment. This week I prefer Salah, next week I will prefer Haaland (Burnley at home) and I wonder if the answer is actually to own both. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Ahead of Gameweek 6, I plan to have both in my team and with enough good budget players this year I think its a legit option. Owning both however could block moves for players that I like and want to own long term like Cole Palmer, Viktor Gyokeres and Arsenal defenders so whilst I think both works now, in might not look optimal in a months time. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">The wildcard button can always be your get out of jail free card if things go wrong though right?</p>

Picking the right captain more often that not, planning ahead to bring in players with good fixture swings, reacting to data and eye test scouting all play a role in having a good season, as well as having luck on your side of course.</p>

class="ssrcss-rcvhal-ServerSideTime e14e9ror0"><span data-testid="timestamp" class="ssrcss-umer6k-Timestamp ekpio9q4"><span data-testid="accessible-timestamp" class="visually-hidden edrdn950"/></span></span><span><strong>Thomas Woods</strong><br/>BBC Sport FPL writer, best finish 9,100th</span></p>
      <p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Despite being burned by him last time out, we still can&#x27;t find a place for Erling Haaland - fresh from two Manchester derby goals - in the FPL team of the week.</p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Like most weeks, it is a choice between the two big guns - Haaland and Mohamed Salah.</p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">While Liverpool forward Salah has eight goals in 11 games against opponents Everton, Haaland faces an Arsenal defence that has yet to concede from open play. It feels like a simple decision.</p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">What you do long term with those two assets is a different question, and FPL expert Gianni Buttice and the team from the FPL Podcast from BBC Sport will be debating that in Friday morning&#x27;s Talking Point article. Keep an eye out for that one.</p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10"><b class="ssrcss-cgjb6m-Keyword e2vephq0">Team cost: 97m</b></p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10"><i class="ssrcss-v0hwvi-AlternateVoice e1geeobk0">The team of the week is selected based on current FPL prices to fit within a 100m budget, as if you were playing a Free Hit.</i></p><figure class="ssrcss-12gl1u2-StyledFigure e34k3c22"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-1v5rnt2-Placeholder etlorgc0"><img alt="Team of the Week" src="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/640/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp" srcSet="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/240/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp 240w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/320/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp 320w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/480/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp 480w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/592/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp 592w" width="592" height="732" class="ssrcss-11yxrdo-Image edrdn950"/></span></div></figure>

      <figure class="ssrcss-12gl1u2-StyledFigure e34k3c22"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-1h9ata-Placeholder etlorgc0"><img alt="Maxence Lacroix" src="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/640/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/0c8a2710-d74a-409f-bffe-cba3c31ba7f0.jpg.webp" srcSet="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/240/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/0c8a2710-d74a-409f-bffe-cba3c31ba7f0.jpg.webp 240w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/320/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/0c8a2710-d74a-409f-bffe-cba3c31ba7f0.jpg.webp 320w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/480/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/0c8a2710-d74a-409f-bffe-cba3c31ba7f0.jpg.webp 480w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/624/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/0c8a2710-d74a-409f-bffe-cba3c31ba7f0.jpg.webp 624w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/800/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/0c8a2710-d74a-409f-bffe-cba3c31ba7f0.jpg.webp 800w" width="811" height="456" class="ssrcss-11yxrdo-Image edrdn950"/></span><span role="text" class="ssrcss-2z7a81-StyledFigureCopyright e34k3c20"><span class="visually-hidden ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e16en2lz0">Image source, </span>Getty Images</span></div></figure><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10"><b class="ssrcss-cgjb6m-Keyword e2vephq0">Chris: Is captaining a defender viable this week? The fixtures don&#x27;t look like they have high-scoring potential. For example, Maxence Lacroix could have a base of four points with Defcon, eight with clean sheet and 14 with a goal from a corner, which West Ham have been poor at defending. Plus bonus! </b></p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">We speak about a player&#x27;s ceiling when considering captaincy but we should also consider their floor now as you rightly point out Chris, because Defcon has changed the game. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Players like Lacroix hit the additional two Defcon points more often than not and I understand why you would consider him. 

There are very few standout fixtures to chase this week but I always prefer to captain the attacker and can probably count on one hand the amount of times Ive captained a defender in over 10 years of playing. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Mo Salah, Antoine Semenyo, Erling Haaland and Cole Palmer are my favourite options this week.</p>

Ekitike or if playing the free hit chip is the play?</b></p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Ekitike has the better fixtures but a start isnt guaranteed and 90 minutes is very unlikely I come to you with the age-old question: Mo Salah or Erling Haaland? </b></p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">This one feels impossible to answer at the moment. This week I prefer Salah, next week I will prefer Haaland (Burnley at home) and I wonder if the answer is actually to own both. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Ahead of Gameweek 6, I plan to have both in my team and with enough good budget players this year I think its a legit option. Owning both however could block moves for players that I like and want to own long term like Cole Palmer, Viktor Gyokeres and Arsenal defenders so whilst I think both works now, in might not look optimal in a months time. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">The wildcard button can always be your get out of jail free card if things go wrong though right?</p>

      <figure class="ssrcss-12gl1u2-StyledFigure e34k3c22"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-4b4v50-Placeholder etlorgc0"><img alt="Alexander Isak and Hugo Ekitike" src="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/640/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/6298f3d4-f750-4d96-b594-7ed6eb6e5239.jpg.webp" srcSet="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/240/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/6298f3d4-f750-4d96-b594-7ed6eb6e5239.jpg.webp 240w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/320/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/6298f3d4-f750-4d96-b594-7ed6eb6e5239.jpg.webp 320w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/480/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/6298f3d4-f750-4d96-b594-7ed6eb6e5239.jpg.webp 480w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/624/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/6298f3d4-f750-4d96-b594-7ed6eb6e5239.jpg.webp 624w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/698/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/6298f3d4-f750-4d96-b594-7ed6eb6e5239.jpg.webp 698w" width="698" height="392" class="ssrcss-11yxrdo-Image edrdn950"/></span><span role="text" class="ssrcss-2z7a81-StyledFigureCopyright e34k3c20"><span class="visually-hidden ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e16en2lz0">Image source, </span>Getty Images</span></div></figure><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10"><b class="ssrcss-cgjb6m-Keyword e2vephq0">Stephen: I believe Alexander Isak will outscore Hugo Ekitike, who I have now, over the season but should I swap them before this weekend or wait? I have the money. </b></p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Arne Slot didnt give much away in his presser this morning and I expect the two forwards will split minutes in the derby. Predicting which one gets the start and a likely 60-75 minutes is very difficult. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">I think I would make the move in the next few weeks but this week I would roll the dice with Ekitike knowing he didnt start in the week and then save the transfer.</p>

class="ssrcss-rcvhal-ServerSideTime e14e9ror0"><span data-testid="timestamp" class="ssrcss-umer6k-Timestamp ekpio9q4"><span data-testid="accessible-timestamp" class="visually-hidden edrdn950"/></span></span><span><strong>Thomas Woods</strong><br/>BBC Sport FPL writer, best finish 9,100th</span></p>
      <p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Despite being burned by him last time out, we still can&#x27;t find a place for Erling Haaland - fresh from two Manchester derby goals - in the FPL team of the week.</p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Like most weeks, it is a choice between the two big guns - Haaland and Mohamed Salah.</p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">While Liverpool forward Salah has eight goals in 11 games against opponents Everton, Haaland faces an Arsenal defence that has yet to concede from open play. It feels like a simple decision.</p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">What you do long term with those two assets is a different question, and FPL expert Gianni Buttice and the team from the FPL Podcast from BBC Sport will be debating that in Friday morning&#x27;s Talking Point article. Keep an eye out for that one.</p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10"><b class="ssrcss-cgjb6m-Keyword e2vephq0">Team cost: 97m</b></p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10"><i class="ssrcss-v0hwvi-AlternateVoice e1geeobk0">The team of the week is selected based on current FPL prices to fit within a 100m budget, as if you were playing a Free Hit.</i></p><figure class="ssrcss-12gl1u2-StyledFigure e34k3c22"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-1v5rnt2-Placeholder etlorgc0"><img alt="Team of the Week" src="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/640/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp" srcSet="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/240/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp 240w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/320/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp 320w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/480/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp 480w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/592/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp 592w" width="592" height="732" class="ssrcss-11yxrdo-Image edrdn950"/></span></div></figure>

class="ssrcss-j37a1a-SubheadlineWrap e14e9ror3"><p class="ssrcss-16yshci-Paragraph e14e9ror4"><span role="text" class="ssrcss-189b1h2-HeadlineWrap e14e9ror2">FPL Q&amp;A with Gianni Buttice</span></p></span></span></header><p class="ssrcss-8kvzjk-Contributor etflsgg2"><span class="ssrcss-1gp5o89-ImageWrapper etflsgg1"><span class="ssrcss-1105681-Placeholder etlorgc0"><img alt="" edrdn950"/></span></span><span><strong>Gianni Buttice</strong><br/>FPL expert and eight-time top-50k finisher</span></p>
      <figure class="ssrcss-12gl1u2-StyledFigure e34k3c22"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-1h9ata-Placeholder etlorgc0"><img alt="Maxence Lacroix" src="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/640/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/0c8a2710-d74a-409f-bffe-cba3c31ba7f0.jpg.webp" srcSet="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/240/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/0c8a2710-d74a-409f-bffe-cba3c31ba7f0.jpg.webp 240w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/320/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/0c8a2710-d74a-409f-bffe-cba3c31ba7f0.jpg.webp 320w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/480/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/0c8a2710-d74a-409f-bffe-cba3c31ba7f0.jpg.webp 480w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/624/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/0c8a2710-d74a-409f-bffe-cba3c31ba7f0.jpg.webp 624w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/800/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/0c8a2710-d74a-409f-bffe-cba3c31ba7f0.jpg.webp 800w" width="811" height="456" class="ssrcss-11yxrdo-Image edrdn950"/></span><span role="text" class="ssrcss-2z7a81-StyledFigureCopyright e34k3c20"><span class="visually-hidden ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e16en2lz0">Image source, </span>Getty Images</span></div></figure><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10"><b class="ssrcss-cgjb6m-Keyword e2vephq0">Chris: Is captaining a defender viable this week? The fixtures don&#x27;t look like they have high-scoring potential. For example, Maxence Lacroix could have a base of four points with Defcon, eight with clean sheet and 14 with a goal from a corner, which West Ham have been poor at defending. Plus bonus! </b></p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">We speak about a player&#x27;s ceiling when considering captaincy but we should also consider their floor now as you rightly point out Chris, because Defcon has changed the game. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Players like Lacroix hit the additional two Defcon points more often than not and I understand why you would consider him. 

There are very few standout fixtures to chase this week but I always prefer to captain the attacker and can probably count on one hand the amount of times Ive captained a defender in over 10 years of playing. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Mo Salah, Antoine Semenyo, Erling Haaland and Cole Palmer are my favourite options this week.</p>

      <figure class="ssrcss-12gl1u2-StyledFigure e34k3c22"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-5zsoxt-Placeholder etlorgc0"><img alt="A graphic showing Mo Salah and Erling Haaland" src="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/640/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/6f8e3573-c22e-44dc-96c9-8e63624587e7.png.webp" srcSet="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/240/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/6f8e3573-c22e-44dc-96c9-8e63624587e7.png.webp 240w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/320/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/6f8e3573-c22e-44dc-96c9-8e63624587e7.png.webp 320w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/480/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/6f8e3573-c22e-44dc-96c9-8e63624587e7.png.webp 480w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/624/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/6f8e3573-c22e-44dc-96c9-8e63624587e7.png.webp 624w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/800/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/19/6f8e3573-c22e-44dc-96c9-8e63624587e7.png.webp 800w" width="1600" height="900" class="ssrcss-11yxrdo-Image edrdn950"/></span><span role="text" class="ssrcss-2z7a81-StyledFigureCopyright e34k3c20"><span class="visually-hidden ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e16en2lz0">Image source, </span>Getty Images</span></div></figure><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10"><b class="ssrcss-cgjb6m-Keyword e2vephq0">Franek: Afternoon, Gianni. I come to you with the age-old question: Mo Salah or Erling Haaland? </b></p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">This one feels impossible to answer at the moment. This week I prefer Salah, next week I will prefer Haaland (Burnley at home) and I wonder if the answer is actually to own both. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Ahead of Gameweek 6, I plan to have both in my team and with enough good budget players this year I think its a legit option. Owning both however could block moves for players that I like and want to own long term like Cole Palmer, Viktor Gyokeres and Arsenal defenders so whilst I think both works now, in might not look optimal in a months time. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">The wildcard button can always be your get out of jail free card if things go wrong though right?</p>

I have the money. </b></p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Arne Slot didnt give much away in his presser this morning and I expect the two forwards will split minutes in the derby. Predicting which one gets the start and a likely 60-75 minutes is very difficult. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">I think I would make the move in the next few weeks but this week I would roll the dice with Ekitike knowing he didnt start in the week and then save the transfer.</p>

Picking the right captain more often that not, planning ahead to bring in players with good fixture swings, reacting to data and eye test scouting all play a role in having a good season, as well as having luck on your side of course.</p>

edrdn950"/></span></span><span><strong>Thomas Woods</strong><br/>BBC Sport FPL writer, best finish 9,100th</span></p>
      <p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Despite being burned by him last time out, we still can&#x27;t find a place for Erling Haaland - fresh from two Manchester derby goals - in the FPL team of the week.</p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Like most weeks, it is a choice between the two big guns - Haaland and Mohamed Salah.</p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">While Liverpool forward Salah has eight goals in 11 games against opponents Everton, Haaland faces an Arsenal defence that has yet to concede from open play. It feels like a simple decision.</p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">What you do long term with those two assets is a different question, and FPL expert Gianni Buttice and the team from the FPL Podcast from BBC Sport will be debating that in Friday morning&#x27;s Talking Point article. Keep an eye out for that one.</p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10"><b class="ssrcss-cgjb6m-Keyword e2vephq0">Team cost: 97m</b></p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10"><i class="ssrcss-v0hwvi-AlternateVoice e1geeobk0">The team of the week is selected based on current FPL prices to fit within a 100m budget, as if you were playing a Free Hit.</i></p><figure class="ssrcss-12gl1u2-StyledFigure e34k3c22"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-1v5rnt2-Placeholder etlorgc0"><img alt="Team of the Week" src="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/640/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp" srcSet="https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/240/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp 240w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/320/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp 320w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/480/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp 480w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/ace/standard/592/cpsprodpb/vivo/live/images/2025/9/18/feb73d09-e4c8-4a75-844b-2531f0598646.jpg.webp 592w" width="592" height="732" class="ssrcss-11yxrdo-Image edrdn950"/></span></div></figure>

The fixtures don&#x27;t look like they have high-scoring potential. For example, Maxence Lacroix could have a base of four points with Defcon, eight with clean sheet and 14 with a goal from a corner, which West Ham have been poor at defending. Plus bonus! </b></p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">We speak about a player&#x27;s ceiling when considering captaincy but we should also consider their floor now as you rightly point out Chris, because Defcon has changed the game. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Players like Lacroix hit the additional two Defcon points more often than not and I understand why you would consider him. 

There are very few standout fixtures to chase this week but I always prefer to captain the attacker and can probably count on one hand the amount of times Ive captained a defender in over 10 years of playing. </p><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Mo Salah, Antoine Semenyo, Erling Haaland and Cole Palmer are my favourite options this week.</p>
